DOS version of ''Ultima IV'' is available for [[Freeware|free]] through [[GOG.com]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2011/09/01/ultima-iv-is-free-on-gog-right-now/|title=Ultima IV Is Free On GoG Right Now|last=Rossignol|first=Jim|work=[[Rock Paper Shotgun]]|date=2011-09-01|access-date=2016-11-04}}</ref> Publisher and IP owner [[Electronic Arts]] has released the game as freeware in 2011 to promote its [[free-to-play]] [[Video game remake|remake]] ''[[Ultima Forever: Quest for the Avatar]]'',<ref name="Mitchell2011">{{cite web|url=https://www.engadget.com/2011/06/03/ultima-4-now-free-ea-launches-ultimaforever-com/|title=Ultima 4 now free, EA launches UltimaForever.com|last=Mitchell|first=Richard|date=3 June 2011|work=[[Engadget]]|access-date=24 May 2018}}</ref> which it would release in 2013.

